            review: "Overall good course with interesting content. The first half more about mathematical foundation of bayesian formula and also quick intro to different sampling algorithm. Second half doing actual bayesian statistics. This semester the TAs kindly provide several python notebooks illustrating how to implement those regressions with PyMC and those materials were extremely helpful. The drawbacks is that PyMC (unfortunately this is out of our control) doesn't seem to be a very matured/well-written package and it reports error messages very hard to understand/debug sometimes.",
