            review: "The first half of the course is very math-heavy (as expected). For someone like me who had a BA and the last math class I took was in high school, I found it challenging but doable if you are good at self-learning. It will be time-consuming because the video lecture doesn't necessarily provide all the details and thought processes. So go on Piazza or Slack, TA and classmates are very useful and they are the main reason I succeed in this class with an A.\nThe second half of the course used a lot of Winbugs. Though in the lecture, the most demonstration is on Winbugs or Matlab, for assignments we have the flexibility to use Python or R. The inconvenient part is in order to understand I would need to translate the Winbugs code into python/R and mistakes can be made during that process.\nOverall, the content itself is useful. My work uses Bayesian so it gave a comprehensive background on the math behind and the application. The structure of this class is frustrating so it really requires you to be an active learner.",
