            reviewDate: 'April 5, 2021',
            semester: 'spring 2021',
            review: "The class was not that easy as many people indicated here from previous semesters. I would have trouble working out the homework problems on my own without Greg's help.  The midterm was pretty hard, maybe just for this semester. I spent over 20 hours working on the 1st part of Q3, one of the most memorable tests I have ever experienced.\nThe hardest part of this course was with the lecture slides. It took lots of effort to have a real understanding or to build the intuitions. For this class, I actually wished Brani could spend more time deliberating on some subjects. Overall, it feels like something was missing. The materials were there, practical and useful, but I was stuck at the stage of primitive imitation. More busy work than meaningful thinking.\nTAs were nice. The grading was generous. A final grade of A should be expected.",
            rating: 3,
            difficulty: 4,
