            review: "This course could be way better if it moved away from using BUGS as many have already mentioned. Take the time to learn the material using a modern Python/R package of your choice (e.g. PyMC3) as that will pay more dividends in the longterm. I did this and it took much more time to complete later homeworks and exams as a result. Early homeworks are very math-heavy while later ones involve mostly programming. Also, the lectures aren't great and the ones that detail a BUGS program are basically unwatchable. I'm expecting to get an A but I definitely put more time in to consciously avoid BUGS",
